common_issues.title: Pieces OS: Issues with Selection, Dependencies, and Authentication
common_issues.description: Users report persistent selection issues, including unintended selection with arrow keys and mouse clicks, preventing copy-pasting.  Additionally, the "Ensure core dependencies" step fails during installation on Linux.  Authentication problems also arise, with users unable to access Pro features despite purchasing memberships. Troubleshooting steps include checking system settings, reinstalling the application, and verifying account credentials.

common_issues.title: Pieces software incompatibility issues across platforms
common_issues.description: Users are experiencing incompatibility issues with Pieces software components, including the Raycast extension, across macOS, Linux, and Windows.  The Raycast extension is not compatible with recent Raycast versions, causing errors. On Linux, the "Ensure core dependencies" step fails during setup.  Windows users are facing authentication problems, hindering Pro membership access.  Suggested solutions include updating the Raycast extension, troubleshooting dependencies on Linux, and verifying login credentials on Windows.

common_issues.title: Authentication Errors in Pieces OS Desktop App
common_issues.description: Users are experiencing authentication errors when attempting to sign in to the Pieces OS desktop app across different operating systems (Windows, Linux).  Issues range from new user sign-in failures to problems with existing Pro accounts.  Suggested troubleshooting includes checking firewall settings, trying different browsers, and ensuring core dependencies are met during installation.

related_issues.text:
An error occurred in the authentication flow.
### Checked for Existing Issues?

- [x] Yes, I have checked existing issues and cannot find one related to this.

### Software

Desktop Application, Pieces OS

### Operating System / Platform

Windows

### Your Pieces OS Version

12.0.0

### Early Access Program

- [ ] Yes, this is related to an Early Access Program feature.

### Kindly describe the bug and include as much detail as possible on what you were doing so we can reproduce the bug.

Hello,
I am receiving this message when attempting to sign-in to Pieces.

```
An error occurred in the authentication flow.
Authentication Error ID: 00000000000000000000000000000000
```

This is a new install. (.appinstaller files)
I have never used the software before.
I do not have a pieces account (yet).
Environment: Windows 11

Launched the authentication by clicking the Sign In button in the Desktop App (4.2.1)
The auth link opened Firefox and generated the error.

I tried the following:
Disabling all extensions in Firefox
Changing my default browser to Edge and re-launching using Edge.
Re-installing with the .exe files.
Reviewed the windows firewall config (Pieces added it itself)
Looked at the Pieces log file but did not see anything obvious enough that I could solve on my own. (See attached)

[log-06252025-copy.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/20907036/log-06252025-copy.txt)

Thank you for the help.

common_issues.title: Users unable to upgrade to Pro or login
common_issues.description: Multiple users report issues with upgrading to the Pro version.  A blank checkout page with zero values appears, then an error. Others cannot authenticate or utilize their Pro membership after purchase.  This affects macOS and Windows users on Pieces OS 12.1.1. Suggested troubleshooting: Check authentication services, verify payment processing, and examine upgrade workflows.

common_issues.title: LTM performance degrades over time, becomes unresponsive
common_issues.description: Users report LTM queries becoming slow and eventually failing after weeks of use.  Issue occurs on macOS and potentially other platforms. Clearing LTM data via the UI is unsuccessful.  Workaround involves removing all Pieces data, but the problem reoccurs. Potential solutions include LTM optimization or data management strategies.

related_issues.title: LTM gets gunged up over time
related_issues.text:
LTM gets gunged up over time
### Checked for Existing Issues?

- [x] Yes, I have checked existing issues and cannot find one related to this.

### Software

Desktop Application

### Operating System / Platform

macOS

### Your Pieces OS Version

12.1.1

### Early Access Program

- [ ] Yes, this is related to an Early Access Program feature.

### Kindly describe the bug and include as much detail as possible on what you were doing so we can reproduce the bug.

So when I freshly install Pieces, the LTM works fine.

When I've had it running for a few weeks, and I want to query the LTM, the query takes forever, and returns nothing.

The same happens via the MCP.

I use my machine all day, so there's a lot of context going into the LTM. The only explanation I can come up with is that it's just getting too big. The Workstream is, however, updating fine.

Removing all my Pieces data gets the LTM working again, but then I end up with this situation later. This is the third time I've been through this loop. It's really frustrating, because when I actually need the LTM, it fails.

The Clear LTM Data button doesn't work, just returning to Try again, from All Data to even for just clearing an hour of data.

I haven't cleared the LTM (well, I've tried, but the Clear LTM Data button doesn't work) so we have a live broken environment to debug with. I'm more than happy to assist with debugging this - let me know what you need!

recommendations: Prioritize resolving authentication issues across Windows and Linux, focusing on firewall settings, browser compatibility, and core dependency checks during installation.
Investigate and address the persistent selection bug in Pieces OS on Windows, ensuring proper functionality of arrow keys and mouse clicks.
Update the Raycast extension for compatibility with the latest Raycast versions.
Troubleshoot and resolve the "Ensure core dependencies" failure during Pieces OS installation on Linux.
Investigate and fix the blank checkout page issue during Pro upgrade, ensuring correct pricing and transaction processing.
Address the LTM performance degradation by optimizing queries and implementing data management strategies to prevent unresponsiveness.
Improve the "Clear LTM Data" functionality in the UI to allow users to effectively manage LTM data.
